thread.title: 1 dead, 1 critically hurt in I-90 crash near Snoqualmie
thread.title_full: 1 dead, 1 critically hurt in I-90 crash near Snoqualmie | The Seattle Times

author: Dominic Gates
title: 1 dead, 1 critically hurt in I-90 crash near Snoqualmie
text:
One person was killed and another critically injured Saturday afternoon when a vehicle went off the highway on eastbound I-90 near Snoqualmie and smashed into another that was parked on the shoulder.
Washington State Patrol Trooper Chris Webb said the parked vehicle was on the left shoulder of the highway, with one person inside and one standing outside, when it was hit by the second vehicle shortly after 2:30 p.m.
Both people with the parked vehicle were critically injured and taken to Harborview Medical Center, where one died less than two hours later.
Webb said the driver of the vehicle that crashed into the parked one was not seriously hurt.
 Boy hurt in fall at Taylor Swift concert at CenturyLink Detectives are investigating the cause of the crash as a possible felony, Webb said, meaning that the driver of the moving vehicle may have been driving “in a dangerous or reckless manner.”
“At this point, we don’t believe alcohol or drugs were involved,” Webb added.
The identity of those involved was not immediately available.
